07/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia's new budget, adopted early on Friday (5 March), is based on estimates of slower growth in 2004. 
The country's GDP is expected to grow by 3.5 per cent, compared to 5 per cent in 2003. 
The government also expects a budget deficit of 4.5 per cent, matching the figure for 2003. 
Inflation was forecast at 2.5 per cent.
In other news, two Croatian generals indicted on war crimes charges are reportedly planning to surrender after consultations with the UN war crimes tribunal. 
Generals Mladen Markac and Ivan Cermak will make a public statement on Monday, sources say. 
(AFP, HINA, BBC, B92 - 05/03/04)
